# Phase 10.6 — alphabetical task order

When planning or implementing **Phase 10.6** work (`plans/Phase-10.6-Architecture-Overhaul.md`):

1. Walk tasks in **strict ID order**: **A1 → A2 → … → A27**, then **B1 → …**, then **C1 → …**, then **D**, **E**, **F**, **G**.
2. Skip rows that are fully **✓** (with verified note where used).
3. **Finish the current row completely** (Status is **✓** with verified date, and behaviour matches the task text) **before** starting the next ID. Treat **Partial** as **not done**: do not open **A7** while **A6** is Partial, do not start **B** while any **A** row is still open, and so on—unless the user explicitly overrides in chat.
4. Do not jump to later letters (e.g. **C19**) while an earlier letter still has any row that is not **✓**.

Cross-repo order still respects this ID sequence (pick the repo that owns the next open row).
